title: Dyer's Record Book, 1867–68
creditline: Gift of Frederick J. Whitehead from the collection compiled by his father Cornelius Whitehead at the Pacific Print Works of Lawrence, Massachusetts
description: Notebook with handwritten formulas for dyestuffs to be used for printing textiles. Contains 218 samples in various designs and brilliant colors. Label on cover reads: "DELAINS FOR 1867-68."

tombstone.epitaph: Dyer's Record Book, 1867–68. Medium: cardboard binding, cotton samples. Gift of Frederick J. Whitehead from the collection compiled by his father Cornelius Whitehead at the Pacific Print Works of Lawrence, Massachusetts. 1945-55-3.
